-- Ghana Increases Daily Minimum Wage to $2.65, Graphic Reports
-- B y   M o s e s   M o z a r t   D z a w u
-- 2012-02-09T09:31:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-09/ghana-increases-daily-minimum-wage-to-2-65-graphic-reports.html
Ghana  has increased the daily minimum
wage by 20 percent to 4.48 cedis ($2.65) with effect from today,
the Accra-based Daily Graphic newspaper reported, citing Enoch
Teye Mensah, the minister of employment and social welfare.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 